  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance covers a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research contexts to support ventricular assist device design decisions, providing absolute hemolysis index estimates under physiological operating conditions. All thirteen ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been evaluated against Model Risk Level 5 requirements. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across key boundary condition inputs. The assessment team concluded that the achieved credibility levels, while below required thresholds for several factors, are sufficient for the intended low-risk advisory use of the model output in the current study phase. No structured context-of-use record is attached to this package; the scope of intended use is described informally in accompanying study documentation.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-fda-centrifugal-pump",
